{
  "text": "The B cell lymphoma-2 (Bcl2) family of proteins are vital controllers of apoptosis [CITATION_1] and they are expressed in solid tumors, including breast, prostate, colorectal, lung, stomach, and ovarian cancers [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . There is increasing proof to recommend that Bcl2-targeting therapy may be an effective treatment for cancers [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
